    'description' => 'Cross-process file locking using PHP\'s flock(). Provides exclusive (write) and shared (read) locks on named lock files in the workspace. Supports: \'acquire_exclusive\' (wait for exclusive lock), \'acquire_shared\' (wait for shared lock), \'release\' (unlock), \'try_exclusive\' (non-blocking exclusive), \'try_shared\' (non-blocking shared). Uses PHP\'s flock() with LOCK_EX/LOCK_SH/LOCK_UN flags. First cross-process coordination primitive in the ecosystem — enables mutexes, read-write locks, and concurrency control between independent tool calls. Never throws — all errors returned as structured data.',
